One of the best instructors who can clarify to the roots (within the scope of the lesson/syllabus) however twisted a question/doubt is shot at him. Unequivocally knows the stuff inside and out and teaches in a very cogent way that invokes appreciation for the subject. Glad to have been his student despite finding TT-2 and the final a bit hard.
Clear teacher, fair tester. Tends to deviate from the textbook but provides you with his own notes which are much easier to read. Probably the best prof I've ever had.
Good prof

This prof has some great teaching skills and is also apparently extremely good at basketball (for his age).  He has recently bought a new omega watch so that obsession has FINALLY ended.  Now he has moved on to a site called www.midomi.com where you can sing a song and it will find it.  Imagine how that is.  Anyway, he's my dad. :)

WAYNE GRETZKY!??!  TRU DAT to the guy who said he's a nutcase on the bball court at HArt House.  I played pick up with him 1 time and he's very crazy, physical and competitive. He was boring at first, but he got much better after a few lectures. He was an easygoing professor, and while he talked a bit too fast for notes (he doesn't write much on the board either) the pace of the material was comfortable. Exam was somewhat easy. Good professor!
One of the better profs at UofT. Pretty funny and witty guy, and fairly approachable.
Knows his stuff and teaches it well.  Go ahead and ask pretty much any electronics question.
